This paper discusses a framework and tool for inferring high-level intents from low-level network behavior. The paper focuses on network behavior and forwarding patterns, which suggests that the most likely sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). However, the paper also discusses verification and synthesis techniques, which are common in the sub-categories of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also uses machine learning techniques to infer intents, which is relevant to the sub-categories of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NI, followed by cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.SI, and cs.DS.
